cui_name: Respiratory syncytial virus (RSV) infection in conditions classified elsewhere and of unspecified site
reasoning: RSV infections are highly prevalent globally, particularly in children. This ICD-10 classification variant for RSV in other conditions with unspecified site is estimated at ~4.5 per 100k per year globally, lower than primary RSV bronchiolitis/pneumonia due to its secondary/complication nature. Based on epidemiological surveillance data and clinical reports.
